        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>heat-distributing units [300052235], HVAC components [300052683], system components [300242031], components by specific context [300241584], components (objects parts) [300241583], Components (hierarchy name) [300241490], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Architectural components, generally in passive solar systems, designed to store heat energy, usually radiated back into spaces as ambient temperature drops; derived from and may also be used for the amount of potential heat storage capacity available in a given component or system.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para componentes arquitectónicos, generalmente en sistemas solares pasivos, diseñados para almacenar energía caliente, generalmente en un techo radiado. Y pueden también ser usados y medidos por la cantidad de calor potencial y capacidad de almacenamiento disponible en un componente o sistema determinado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor  bouwkundige componenten, meestal in passieve zonnesystemen, die ontworpen zijn om warmte-energie op te slaan welke gewoonlijk wordt teruggestraald in ruimten wanneer de omgevingstemperatuur daalt. Het woord is afgeleid van en mag ook gebruikt worden voor de potentiële warmteopslagcapaciteit die beschikbaar is in een bepaalde component of bepaald systeem.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Architektonisches Bauelement, üblicherweise in passiven Solaranlagen, das dem Zweck dient, Wärmeenergie zu speichern, die normalerweise in den Raum abgestrahlt würde, wenn die Umgebungstemperatur absinkt; abgeleitet von und verwendet für die potenzielle Wärmekapazität eines bestimmten Bauelementes oder Systems.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
